  "active_lock_reason": null,
  "body": "If we have a validator that has been slashed, voluntarily exited, or we just don't want it to be included when we run any of the validator client features, maybe we should have an option to delete the validator from local storage in the CLI.\r\n\r\nSo far, I've just been deleting locally (e.g. `rm ~/.local/share/lodestar/prater/secrets/0x1234...` and the same for the `keystores` dir).  This functionality would basically just be a helper for that process.\r\n\r\n",
